WEBVTT	#Elemental Media Engine(TM) 2.17.0.0

00:00:00.00 --> 00:00:03.33
- Now President Biden's top UN Envoy Ambassador Linda

00:00:03.33 --> 00:00:07.41
Thomas-Greenfield told CBS News that the US will respond very

00:00:07.41 --> 00:00:09.93
swiftly should the situation deteriorate.

00:00:09.93 --> 00:00:13.38
She says there's no evidence of Russia moving some troops away

00:00:13.38 --> 00:00:14.19
from the border.

00:00:14.19 --> 00:00:17.16
She spoke with CBS News Foreign Affairs Analyst Pamela

00:00:17.16 --> 00:00:20.94
Falk, where she urged Americans to get out

00:00:20.94 --> 00:00:24.18
while there is still time.

00:00:24.18 --> 00:00:24.68
AMB.

00:00:24.68 --> 00:00:27.54
LINDA THOMAS-GREENFIELD: We would welcome the Russians

00:00:27.54 --> 00:00:30.96
moving some of their troops across the border, but we've--

00:00:30.96 --> 00:00:34.11
away from the border, but we've seen no evidence of that, Pam.

00:00:34.11 --> 00:00:38.34
And they still have hundreds plus thousand troops

00:00:38.34 --> 00:00:41.85
on the border with Ukraine as we speak.

00:00:41.85 --> 00:00:45.69
And those troops are threatening the independence

00:00:45.69 --> 00:00:49.51
and the sovereignty of this country.

00:00:49.51 --> 00:00:56.01
And so we want the Russians to accept a diplomatic way

00:00:56.01 --> 00:01:01.32
forward, a discussion at the negotiating table

00:01:01.32 --> 00:01:04.74
that will address their security concerns

00:01:04.74 --> 00:01:07.75
and address the security concerns of Europe

00:01:07.75 --> 00:01:10.89
and of Ukraine moving forward.

00:01:10.89 --> 00:01:14.61
And until that happens, we will continue

00:01:14.61 --> 00:01:17.55
to lean in on diplomacy.

00:01:17.55 --> 00:01:22.50
PAMELA FALK: And diplomatic efforts have been intense.

00:01:22.50 --> 00:01:25.64
Have you spoken with your counterparts?

00:01:25.64 --> 00:01:29.58
And what can the UN do with Russia

00:01:29.58 --> 00:01:32.26
on the Security Council and a veto vote?

00:01:32.26 --> 00:01:32.76
AMB.

00:01:32.76 --> 00:01:33.45
LINDA THOMAS-GREENFIELD: While Russia

00:01:33.45 --> 00:01:35.46
is the president of the council, they

00:01:35.46 --> 00:01:37.86
can't block council actions.

00:01:37.86 --> 00:01:42.45
They can't stop the council from having meetings or discussions

00:01:42.45 --> 00:01:45.72
on the situation as they [INAUDIBLE]

00:01:45.72 --> 00:01:49.62
yesterday during a lunch that they hosted.

00:01:49.62 --> 00:01:53.04
So we hope to continue to engage with them

00:01:53.04 --> 00:01:55.53
on this issue in the council.

00:01:55.53 --> 00:01:58.56
They will certainly make every effort

00:01:58.56 --> 00:02:02.41
to distract us by putting other things on the agenda,

00:02:02.41 --> 00:02:07.44
but we will continue to press on this issue in the council.

00:02:07.44 --> 00:02:11.98
PAMELA FALK: And what does a diplomatic solution look like?

00:02:11.98 --> 00:02:12.48
AMB.

00:02:12.48 --> 00:02:14.31
LINDA THOMAS-GREENFIELD: What it will entail

00:02:14.31 --> 00:02:19.20
is sitting down at the table, talking through the issues

00:02:19.20 --> 00:02:24.63
that the Russians have talking through the issues of Ukraine.

00:02:24.63 --> 00:02:28.54
It's about also talking about the Russians commitment

00:02:28.54 --> 00:02:32.61
or lack thereof to pull their troops out of Crimea.

00:02:32.61 --> 00:02:36.09
It's about sitting down and finding a way forward

00:02:36.09 --> 00:02:39.33
that will address all of our security concerns

00:02:39.33 --> 00:02:43.65
and pull us away from the brink of this confrontation

00:02:43.65 --> 00:02:46.05
that the Russians are responsible for.

00:02:46.05 --> 00:02:50.04
PAMELA FALK: Ambassador are you optimistic that there will

00:02:50.04 --> 00:02:51.68
be a diplomatic way forward?

00:02:51.68 --> 00:02:52.18
AMB.

00:02:52.18 --> 00:02:53.85
LINDA THOMAS-GREENFIELD: Yes, I continue

00:02:53.85 --> 00:02:58.33
to be optimistic that we can find a diplomatic way forward.

00:02:58.33 --> 00:03:00.96
But I have to be honest that we're also

00:03:00.96 --> 00:03:05.37
preparing for something else.

00:03:05.37 --> 00:03:10.80
We're unified in our efforts with our European colleagues

00:03:10.80 --> 00:03:15.99
to forcefully respond and swiftly

00:03:15.99 --> 00:03:19.57
respond to any Russian action.

00:03:19.57 --> 00:03:21.54
But at the same time, we will continue

00:03:21.54 --> 00:03:24.27
to lean in on the diplomacy.

00:03:24.27 --> 00:03:27.51
And as you know, we've been very, very clear

00:03:27.51 --> 00:03:32.19
in our pronouncements concerning American citizens and Ukraine.

00:03:32.19 --> 00:03:36.75
And I just wanted to reiterate that while we're speaking that,

00:03:36.75 --> 00:03:40.62
American citizens should make every effort

00:03:40.62 --> 00:03:43.68
to leave Ukraine while they have the opportunity

00:03:43.68 --> 00:03:45.45
to do so freely.

00:03:45.45 --> 00:03:47.46
You've heard the Secretary of State,

00:03:47.46 --> 00:03:52.44
you've heard that from the National Security advisor,

00:03:52.44 --> 00:03:54.24
as well as from the president.

00:03:54.24 --> 00:04:02.31
But we are preparing to respond as I noted very swiftly should

00:04:02.31 --> 00:04:05.21
the situation deteriorate.